l knowledge is acquired, and&lt;br&gt;
union with the great spirit of the univers=
e is eventually gained. Here&lt;br&gt;
he is &quot;the howling and terrific destr=
oyer of human passions and&lt;br&gt;
physical senses, which are ever in the way o=
f the development of the&lt;br&gt;
higher spiritual perceptions and the growth of=
 the inner eternal man&lt;br&gt;
-- mystically . . . Siva-Rudra is the Destroyer,=
